er%20than%20ever%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20our%20first%20baby%20was%20born%2C%20I%20was%20so%20in%20love%20with%20him%20and%20elated%20to%20finally%20have%20what%20I%20wanted%20most%3A%20to%20be%20a%20mom.%20In%20those%20first%20weeks%2C%20I%20felt%20strongly%20that%20I%20would%20love%20my%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-stay-at-home-mom-reentered-workforce-sales-2025-3%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enew%20role%20as%20a%20stay-at-home%20mom%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20and%20couldn't%20imagine%20going%20back%20to%20work.%20However%2C%20after%20my%20husband's%20paternity%20leave%20ended%20and%20he%20returned%20to%20work%2C%20I%20was%20home%20alone%20with%20the%20baby%2C%20and%20reality%20set%20in.%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-to-know-if-you-sleep-enough-time-2018-5%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20was%20sleep%20deprived%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20exhausted%20from%20exclusively%20nursing%2C%20and%20lonelier%20than%20I%20had%20ever%20been.%20I%20was%20jealous%20of%20my%20friends%20who%20were%20still%20working%20and%20could%20get%20away%20to%20do%20something%20other%20than%20care%20for%20a%20baby.%20Desperate%20for%20connection%2C%20I%20joined%20several%20baby%20and%20me%20classes%20through%20my%20local%20parks%20and%20rec%2C%20hoping%20to%20make%20a%20few%20friends%20navigating%20the%20same%20challenges.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20moms%20I%20met%20were%20kind%2C%20but%20our%20conversations%20revolved%20around%20our%20children's%20sleeping%20and%20eating%20schedules%20and%20how%20we%20were%20dealing%20with%20our%20toddlers'%20tantrums.%20Somewhere%20along%20the%20way%2C%20my%20interests%20and%20identity%20faded%20away.%20I%20needed%20more%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhealth%2Fmental-health%2Fsensory-overload%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eintellectual%20stimulation%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%2C%20I%20wanted%20to%20do%20more%20to%20connect%20with%20the%20community%2C%20and%20I%20wanted%20to%20use%20my%20talents%20outside%20of%20the%20home.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22e3106e67-db21-435e-b3e9-4c7772178ca8%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3EStaying%20home%20wasn't%20for%20me%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAs%20months%20turned%20into%20years%2C%20I%20felt%20increasingly%20isolated.%20I%20hired%20a%20babysitter%20once%20a%20week%20in%20the%20afternoon%20so%20I%20could%20escape%20the%20monotony%20of%20child%20rearing.%20One%20of%20these%20afternoons%2C%20I%20remember%20going%20to%20the%20movies%20alone%20and%20sobbing%20through%20%26quot%3BLa%20La%20Land%2C%26quot%3B%20not%20because%20of%20the%20storyline%20but%20because%20it%20reminded%20me%20of%20what%20it%20felt%20like%20to%20be%20alive%20and%20have%20a%20sense%20of%20self%20outside%20motherhood.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhen%20I%20finally%20summoned%20the%20courage%20to%20talk%20to%20my%20stay-at-home-mom%20friends%20about%20my%20feelings%2C%20it%20felt%20as%20if%20I%20was%20violating%20an%20unspoken%20rule.%20Shouldn't%20I%20be%20grateful%20for%20this%20opportunity%20to%20bond%20with%20my%20child%20without%20the%20stress%20of%20a%20career%3F%20Wasn't%20it%20a%20privilege%20to%20be%20there%20for%20all%20of%20my%20child's%20milestones%3F%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20fact%2C%20I%20knew%20how%20blessed%20I%20was%20to%20be%20able%20to%20stay%20home%20with%20my%20children%2C%20but%20I%20%3Cem%3Estill%3C%2Fem%3E%20felt%20so%20depressed.%20Five%20years%20of%20staying%20home%20and%20two%20babies%20later%2C%20it%20wasn't%20until%20I%20returned%20to%20work%20with%20a%20purpose%20outside%20the%20home%20that%20I%20truly%20felt%20like%20myself%20again.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cbr%3E%3Cspan%3EI%20truly%20love%20being%20a%20mom%2C%20but%20I%20recognize%20that%20staying%20at%20hom