e%20map.%20Texas%20is%20huge!%20I%20mean%2C%20if%20you%20put%20it%20in%20the%20middle%20of%20Europe%2C%20it%20takes%20up%20most%20of%20Europe%20up.%20However%2C%20they%20do%20disaster%20recovery%20very%2C%20very%20well%2C%20and%20so%20does%20Florida.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20FEMA%20employee%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20by%20the%20time%20Richardson%20mentioned%20his%20girlfriend%2C%20more%20than%20a%20dozen%20members%20of%20the%20livestream%20audience%20watching%20from%20their%20office%20had%20begun%20jeering%20loudly%20at%20the%20screen.%20Some%20staff%20members%20began%20walking%20around%20the%20office%20waving%20pencils%20in%20the%20air%2C%20mimicking%20the%20way%20Richardson%20had%20fidgeted%20with%20a%20writing%20utensil%20while%20speaking%2C%20the%20employee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BI've%20never%20seen%20people%20so%20mocking%20of%20an%20agency%20head%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20employee%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIt's%20unclear%20exactly%20how%20much%20of%20FEMA's%20staff%20has%20been%20cut%20since%20Trump%20took%20office%3B%20the%20most%20recent%20estimates%20from%20CNN%20put%20the%20total%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fnumber-workers-fired-doge-trump-musk-challenger-2025-4%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ereduction%20of%20force%3C%2Fa%3E%20at%20about%201%2C000%20workers%2C%20or%20about%2020%25%20of%20FEMA's%20permanent%20full-time%20staff.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20US%20Government%20Accountability%20Office%20reported%20in%202023%20that%20FEMA%20had%20an%20overall%20staffing%20gap%20of%20about%2035%25%2C%20or%206%2C200%20employees%2C%20which%20had%20%26quot%3Baffected%20its%20ability%20to%20achieve%20its%20mission.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20FEMA%20spokesperson%20told%20Business%20Insider%20that%20%26quot%3Bunder%20Secretary%20Noem's%20leadership%2C%20and%20the%20efforts%20of%20Acting%20Administrator%20Richardson%2C%20FEMA%20is%20fully%20activated%20in%20preparation%20for%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fclimate-change-hurricanes-why-storms-are-wetter-stronger-slower-2019-7%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3EHurricane%3C%2Fa%3E%20Season.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20Trump%20administration%20has%20not%20made%20a%20public%20statement%20about%20a%20permanent%20nominee%20to%20lead%20FEMA.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20spokesperson%20added%20that%20%26quot%3Bcomplaints%20about%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Ftrump-return-to-office-rto-mandate-federal-workers-reaction-doge-2025-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Emorale%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20training%2C%20and%20planning%20come%20from%20the%20same%20internal%20class%20that%20resisted%20accountability%20for%20decades.%20This%20is%20just%20another%20example%20of%20a%20long%20line%20of%20internal%20leaks%20from%20people%20who%20clearly%20couldn't%20care%20less%20about%20Americans%20facing%20disaster%20and%20prefer%20to%20manufacture%20petty%20drama%20for%20their%20own%20self-aggrandizement.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20town%20hall%20meeting%2C%20Richardson%20said%20his%20plan%20for%20the%20agency%20is%20to%20follow%20%26quot%3Bthe%20president's%20intent%2C%26quot%3B%20which%20he%20described%20as%20limiting%20FEMA's%20activities%20to%20its%20%26quot%3Bmission%20essential%20tasks.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EOne%20staff%20member%20said%20most%20FEMA%20employees%20are%20determined%20to%20carry%20out%20the%20agency's%20mission.%20%26quot%3BThose%20of%20us%20still%20remaining%20were%20either%20too%20committed%20to%20go%20anywhere%2C%20not%20eligible%20to%20take%20the%20resignation%20options%2C%20or%20so%20committed%20to%20the%20mission%20we%20do%20not%20care%20what%20he%20does%2C%26quot%3B%20they%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fstaff-meeting-fema-administrator-david-richardson-emergency-preparedness-hurricanes-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1747