ot%20of%20perks%2C%20but%20there's%20one%20thing%20I%20really%20don't%20like.%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%225763%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22Women%20working%20at%20a%20table.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F682e30acc6ad288d148194c0%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%223842%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3E%C2%A0%3Cp%3EGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cul%3E%3Cli%3EKate%20Collins%20has%20worked%20on%20an%20all-female%20nonprofit%20team%20since%20starting%20a%20new%20job%20in%202024.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3EIn%20the%20past%2C%20she's%20worked%20in%20male-dominated%20media%20workplaces%20with%20rigid%2C%20then%20lenient%2C%20boundaries.%3C%2Fli%3E%3Cli%3ECollins%20says%20that%20an%20all-female%20team%20brings%20both%20a%20supportive%20culture%20and%20blurred%20work-life%20lines.%3C%2Fli%3E%3C%2Ful%3E%3Cp%3EWhen%20I%20walked%20into%20work%20last%20year%20on%20my%20birthday%2C%20there%20was%20an%20envelope%20with%20my%20name%20written%20in%20cursive%20on%20my%20desk.%20I%20was%20less%20than%20three%20months%20into%20a%20new%20job%20and%20hadn't%20announced%20my%20birthday.%20Being%20an%20introvert%2C%20a%20slight%20discomfort%20rose%20as%20I%20opened%20the%20envelope.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20discomfort%20dissipated%20as%20I%20read%20the%20personalized%20messages%20written%20by%20my%20colleagues.%20I%20was%20grateful%20for%20the%20simple%20gesture%3B%20this%20was%20the%20first%20time%20I%20received%20a%20birthday%20card%20at%20work.%20A%20few%20months%20later%2C%20I%20returned%20from%20my%20honeymoon%20to%20find%20another%20thoughtful%20card%20and%20a%20wedding-decorated%20desk.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EMy%20colleagues'%20acknowledgment%20of%20these%20milestones%20is%20proof%20that%20after%20a%20midlife%20pivot%2C%20I've%20landed%20somewhere%20good.%20The%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpixar-turning-red-all-female-leadership-team-2022-1%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Eall-female%20leadership%20and%20team%3C%2Fa%3E%20where%20I%20work%20prioritize%20the%20organization's%20mission%20by%20fostering%20a%20kind%2C%20encouraging%20atmosphere%20for%20clients%20and%20employees.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20I%20see%20the%20perks%2C%20I've%20also%20experienced%20some%20downsides%20to%20an%20all-female%20workplace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22a137a3a4-7ba7-4b1d-85af-259bfcea9027%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EI%20started%20my%20career%20in%20offices%20with%20boundaries%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20entered%20the%20workforce%20during%20an%20era%20when%20professionalism%20stressed%20a%20clear%20delineation%20between%20work%20and%20personal%20lives.%20In%20the%20offices%20of%20the%20media%20companies%20where%20I%20worked%20as%20a%20photojournalist%20and%20reporter%2C%20employees%20refrained%20from%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsharing-at-work-stop-oversharing-in-office-professional-growth-2023-10%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Edivulging%20details%20of%20their%20outside%20lives%3C%2Fa%3E.%20I%20welcomed%20these%20boundaries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBy%20the%20mid-2010s%2C%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fhow-the-media-has-changed-in-the-last-decade-2019-11%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Esuccessive%20rounds%20of%20layoffs%20in%20my%20industry%3C%2Fa%3E%20resulted%20in%20a%20less%20diverse%20workplace.%20Management%20became%20mostly%20men%20who%20I%20remember%20using%20sports%20analogies%2C%20mansplaining%2C%20and%20all-caps%20emails%20%E2%80%94%20controlling%20tactics%20that%20diminished%20my%20sense%20of%20worth.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EA%20decade%20later%2C%20bias%20issues%20forced%20the%20last%20media%20company%20I%20worked%20for%20to%20adopt%20policies%20stressing%20safe%2C%20inclusive%20workplaces.%20The%20personal%20became%20political%2C%20and%20the%20movement%20to%20normalize%20almost%20everything%20took%20hold.%20Before%20long%2C%20a%20workplace%20culture%20emerged%20where%20revealing%20intimate%20personal%20information%20was%20commonplace.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EYet%20there%20still%20wasn't%20a%20shift%20away%20from%20the%20male-dominated%20culture.%20Many%20of%20my%20female%20colleagues%20who%20survived%20layoffs%20exited%20the%20industry.%20Before%20long%2C%20I%20was%20planning%20my%20own%20exit%20strategy.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%222cdda643-5d22-4938-be56-33a5f5b29e96%5C%22%3EIt%20was%20difficult%20to%20separate%20myself%20from%20a%20profession%20I%20once%20loved%20%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EFor%20a%20few%20years%2C%20I%20worked%20on%20reinventing%20myself%20by%20expanding%20my%20skill%20set%20through%20classes%20and%20freelance%20work.%20I%20was%20eventually%20offered%20an%20environmental%20communications%20position.%20While%20the%20job%20didn't%20last%2C%20it%20launched%20me%20into%20the%20nonprofit%20sector.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI%20live%20in%20a%20region%20with%20many%20nonprofits.%20The%20local%20nonprofits%20I'm%20most%20familiar%20with%20are%20primarily%20led%20and%20staffed%20by%20smart%20women%20passionate%20about%20helping%20others.%20This%20isn't%20surprising%2C%20as%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.researchgate.net%2Fpublication%2F51594567_Gender_Differences_in_Personality_across_the_Ten_Aspects_of_the_Big_Five%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Estudies%20concerning%20the%20differences%20in%20personality%20traits%20have%20found%20that%20women%20are%20more%20nurturing%2C%20tender-minded%2C%20and%20altruistic%20more%20often%20and%20to%20a%20greater%20extent%20than%20men%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%94%20traits%20necessary%20to%20do%20lower-paid%2C%20sometimes%20emotionally%20taxing%20work.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22c8de00b6-bafa-40ba-89e1-b220db93f32a%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EWhen%20I%20started%20nonprofit%20work%2C%20I%20felt%20acknowledged%20and%20supported%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20started%20my%20current%20communications%20manager%20position%20in%20early%202024.%20Since%20transitioning%20to%20nonprofit%20work%2C%20I've%20experienced%20how%20an%20all-female%20team%20can%20promote%20a%20kinder%2C%20more%20collaborative%20workplace.%20Have%20an%20idea%20for%20something%20not%20in%20your%20job%20title%3F%20Share%20it.%20Need%20help%20with%20a%20project%3F%20There%20are%20always%20offers%20to%20assist%2C%20even%20for%20projects%20requiring%20time%20outside%20normal%20schedules.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThere's%20also%20the%20celebration%20of%20achievements.%20Our%20leader%20frequently%20shares%20our%20team%20and%20individual%20accomplishments%20publicly.%20She%20gifted%20us%20with%20bright%20yellow%20smiley%20face%20bells%20to%20ring%20when%20we%20complete%20a%20difficult%20project.%20After%20years%20without%20recognition%20of%20my%20professional%20achievements%2C%20it%20feels%20good%20to%20have%20my%20contributions%20acknowledged.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20professional%20respect%20ingrained%20in%20our%20office%20culture%20extends%20beyond%20job%20tasks.%20If%20we%20come%20in%20late%20or%20leave%20early%20for%20an%20appointment%20or%20emergency%2C%20we%20can%20do%20so%20without%20advance%20approval.%20Leadership%20even%20encourages%20us%20to%20take%20personal%20days%20when%20we're%20feeling%20stressed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20kind%2C%20empathic%20leadership%20style%20trickles%20down.%20Recently%20one%20of%20my%20coworkers%20was%20out%20for%20a%20few%20days%20with%20the%20flu.%20Knowing%20she%20lives%20alone%2C%20we%20reached%20out%20with%20%26quot%3Bget%20well%20soon%26quot%3B%20texts%20and%20offered%20to%20pick%20up%20her%20prescription%20and%20deliver%20it%20to%20her%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%22847df151-6295-4a38-b9f9-5e1ca4aa76e9%5C%22%3E%3Cstrong%3EThere%20are%20also%20challenges%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EWhile%20working%20in%20an%20all-female%20office%20has%20been%20a%20positive%20change%2C%20certain%20aspects%20can%20be%20trying.%20There's%20inherent%20pressure%20to%20participate%20in%20optional%20group%20activities%20such%20as%20weekly%20team%20lunches%20and%20afternoon%20walks%2C%20which%20can%20be%20stressful%20for%20someone%20who%20cherishes%20alone%20time%20like%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERecently%2C%20a%20mandatory%20retreat%20escalated%20into%20a%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fguides%2Fhome%2Fbest-cold-plunge-tubs%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22%5C%22%3Ecold%20plunge%3C%2Fa%3E.%20Voiced%20statements%20about%20not%20liking%20cold%20water%20were%20countered%20with%20emails%20about%20%26quot%3Bteam%20building.%26quot%3B%20Days%20before%2C%20a%20colleague%20said%20that%20she%20couldn't%20partake%20due%20to%20a%20medical%20issue.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20end%2C%20a%20few%20of%20us%20watched%20the%20cold%20plunge%20through%20the%20window%20of%20a%20warm%20house.%20I%20was%20already%20nervous%20about%20an%20overnight%20cabin%20retreat.%20I%20wasn't%20fond%20of%20the%20planned%20kayaking%20and%20swimming%2C%20but%20I%20also%20didn't%20want%20to%20hurt%20the%20feelings%20of%20my%20colleagues%20planning%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20blurring%20of%20lines%20between%20work%20and%20play%20can%20also%20result%20in%20unexpected%20workplace%20tension.%20When%20a%20new%20colleague%20joined%20our%20team%20recently%2C%20she%20misinterpreted%20the%20relaxed%20atmosphere%20as%20%26quot%3Bany%20topic%20goes.%26quot%3B%20While%20I%20appreciate%20an%20informal%20office%2C%20some%20of%20the%20topics%20she%20discussed%20made%20me%20uncomfortable.%20I%20eventually%20spoke%20up%20about%20my%20new%20colleague's%20crudeness%2C%20and%20the%20issue%20was%20addressed.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%20data-toc-id%3D%5C%2226966c6f-ec73-4227-a3fa-ead5fa53793f%5C%22%3EI%20question%20whether%20the%20easing%20of%20professional%20manners%20has%20veered%20too%20far%20off-track%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EI%20wonder%20if%20a%20single-sex%20environment%20contributes%20to%20this.%20I%20wonder%20if%20my%20colleague%20would've%20acted%20differently%20around%20male%20colleagues%20and%20if%20a%20male%20would've%20been%20terminated%20for%20similar%20behavior%20around%20female%20coworkers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EI'm%20not%20looking%20to%20leave%20my%20job.%20If%20I%20ever%20return%20to%20a%20workplace%20with%20both%20men%20and%20women%2C%20I'll%20bring%20what%20I'm%20learning%20about%20collaboration%2C%20kindness%2C%20and%20celebrating%20achievements%20with%20me.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKate%20Collins%20is%20a%20writer%20and%20nonprofit%20communications%20professional.%20She%20lives%20in%20Ithaca%2C%20New%20York%2C%20with%20her%20husband%2C%20stepson%2C%20and%20two%20foster%20dogs.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cdiv%3ERead%20the%20original%20article%20on%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpros-cons-working-all-female-environment-2025-5%5C%22%3EBusiness%20Insider%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fdiv%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1747904702000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F682e30d8c6ad288d148194cd%3Fformat%3Djpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpros-cons-working-all-female-environment-2025-5%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Kate%20Collins%20is%20a%20communications%20manager%20at%20a%20local%20nonprofit.%20Her%20all-female%20team%20is%20encouraging%20but%20can%20sometimes%20overstep%20boundaries.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22insider%40insider.com%20(Kate%20Collins)%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A41%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fpros-cons-working-all-female-environment-2025-5%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22What%20we%20know%20about%20the%20victims%20of%20Washington%20DC%20shooting%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1747904640000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F25%2F05%2F1920x1080%2Fskynews-sarah-yaron_6923846.jpg%3F20250522083910%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fyaron-lischinsky-and-sarah-milgrim-what-we-know-about-washington-dc-shooting-victims-13372549%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20two%20people%20shot%20dead%20in%20Washington%20DC%20on%20Wednesday%20were%20Israeli%20embassy%20workers%20who%20were%20plann